reviews_data.review_text: I like the coffee but not the customer service.
Me and my daughter has been here twice and we have enjoyed our muffins and coffee each time. It is in walking distance to our home. Friendly service and real nice atmosphere

Had to mix up my matcha latte myself at home because they didn't mix it well. They didn't add enough white mocha flavoring and the barista was confused on a very simple order. Would likely not Return to this location
The blueberry muffin was amazing. They even offered to warm them... sadly I got the short end on the quality on my mocha... it wasn't even hot...
The food and drinks are really good and the baristas are really nice!
Good tasting coffee, quick & quality service, and a chill atmosphere
Over priced Bs
Chai tea. Quick service. Friendly staff. Great stop getting out of the rain.
Today I had a pleasure of being served by Isabella & and Andrea! They We're both very sweet and polite!
Tried an espresso and latte + a blueberry muffin. This place is always great.

I was standing at the bar waiting on my coffee and the only person waiting. Instead of telling me my coffee was ready, they all just got back on their phones and continued to scroll. They put my coffee at the other end where you pay instead of on the bar so I had no idea it was ready. Had I not looked for it, I'd still be standing there.

I love this place. And the music playlist 
Very nice job
Highly recommend this coffee shop,  maybe  a little bit expensive but, the coffees and sandwiches are good
I ordered a graham cracker iced latter with oat milk - so good!  Hubby had a macchiato latte and was happy with his also. Water bean is a cute spot!
I ordered a coffee and cookies , the horror of no taste , no service , and the little ones

probably one of the best lattes I've ever had. I tried the graham cracker latte with oat milk  100/10! So so yummy. Perfect combination of sweet and coffee flavor! Also the two girls that were working were so sweet and helpful in their recommendations
Good flavorful coffee, snacks, baked goods, and sandwiches! Always clean and very relaxing environment. Staff is very welcoming and pleasant.
Nice little cafe with good breakfast options. I was lucky to find it open in Black Friday!
Got the bacon egg and cheese on a croissant and the mocha brown sugar latte and they were AMAZING!! can't wait to come back

The breakfast sandwich was good. The coffee is not as expected ! We ordered Latte, There was no foam!
the atmosphere is nice. However, I think the service could be improved. The barista didn't seem very cheerful or welcoming, and as a customer, I expect a bit more warmth and friendliness.

Sunday morning and Mrs. wanted to stop for a coffee. We're here and it's a nice and comfortable space. Plenty of room inside and nice seating outside. A great spot to work on your laptop.

Coffee is delicious. They have sandwiches and pastries, too!

Lovely coffee shop. Has plenty of seating especially outside. We only sampled the macaroons which were very good. Along with a pumpkin cold brew and black regular coffee all photo worthy as well as tasty. Staff was super friendly. Look forward to visiting again.

For a 7 dollar coffee I am very disappointed. I order a Caramel Latte. Not only didn't have any Caramel whatsoever but the milk was almost boiling.
Those who know about coffee knows well that even the milk has to have certain temperature in order to make it taste great.
The place is kind of beautiful and quiet and the ambience was great.
I'm very sorry to write this review but for this price I think they can do a better job specially when the place was almost empty so it is not like they were very busy at the time I ordered.
Sincerely I think there's room for improvement.
Oh, Waterbean! Why did you discontinue the creme brulee latte???

I was tired of Starbucks and Dunkin wanted to try something new. Stopped by Waterbean and it was amazing. The Vanilla Latte with Almond milk was delicious. The prices are a little higher than Dunkin and Starbucks but the drinks taste much better. Try the freshly made breakfast sandwiches they can be customized.
Good coffee. Quick. Pleasant atmosphere. OK prices. Good selection. I tried Pumpkin Spice(decent) and Taro Tea( meh).
Not quality vietnamese coffee.

I've found this place just as I was looking for a place to grab a cup of coffee other than Starbucks and Dunkin after I dropped off my kids at volleyball camp.  And I've been there three straight days!! Their coffee was awesome.  I usually get a latte with oatmilk and it was perfect.  The atmosphere of the store was very open but cozy and bright that makes you want to stay there longer.  I really enjoyed going there!
My coffee was amazing
Great coffee and very good breakfast sandwiches!
Great fresh sandwich. Bagel was very tasty. Affogato, love it !!!
great place
Never acknowledged customers and several people walked out including us
This little coffee shop became our favorite stop on the way to the coast. Great coffee,  good ice-cream. Nice atmosphere.  Shelby ( l hope l got your name right, girl) is a great hostess. Thanks!
Good but I couldn't see the food menu. I don't know, I thought it was weird, but the place is cool.

Coffee is reasonably priced compared to  other big name coffee franchises. First 2 times I went, it was great (drip/ brewed). The third time I ordered the same thing-I don't know what kind of coffee  it was, but it was nasty and had to toss it when I got home. I will go back, but will definitely taste it before I leave. Pastries are typical-Had a cinnamon muffin. Outside seating  available.
Large menu with many different flavors and drink choices! Love the variety of teas
Coffee and service here are amazing. Just moved to the area and need a coffee shop for my morning pick ups. Would recommend!!

I tried Latte and Cappuccino.
For me the Waterbean Latte has been better than Starbucks

Great place.
Busy on a Wednesday for sure.

They had an issue the day we went with one of the two baristas not present, but undoubtedly they'd make good food with a full staff.
Great rice crispy treats!! Iced coffee was good
Friendly staff and good coffee
They gotta work on that customer service
Great coffee. Great employees.

I did not want to write a review because the baristas were very nice and the only reason why I would come back here. This place is disgusting and needs a very deep cleaning and new equipment. As I sat here the other day, I saw a few bugs crawling on the counter by where I was sitting then as I approached the register, I saw a dead bug. This should be addressed immediately because it is gross, how are we supposed to be sitting and eating comfortably when there is roaches around? I will be needing to see a change in the cleanliness at this store before I ever return. All the other Waterbean locations have a much nicer inside. Avoid this one at all costs.
Not very clean and the sitting area was not kept well. I would go back. Needs a major clean and better customer service.
Staff was friendly and took my order and made my coffee then forgot to make my food. It was good once it arrived.

Walked in excited to try a new spot. I never thought in my life a lack of greeting would make
Me wanna leave but it sure did especially after I try to say hello, how are you today? I got stared at with no reply while goes back to picking at fingernails. Im like you k ow what I'll keep my money let's go somewhere we feel welcome.
Best chai tea I've ever had.

Love the feel of this coffee shop. Great quality espresso, lattes and cappuccino better than Starbucks prices and much better quality too. My cinnamon toffee latte was heaven in a cup and just the right amount of caffeine to keep me going.

Excellent coffee, food, WiFi, staff and music.

My go to spot when I'm looking to get some work done outside of my home.

I mean this with the utmost respect because I don't like trashing on service workers, but this was the worse coffee I've ever had. I ordered the iced Vietnamese  Coffee with condensed milk. Literally tasted like water with a splash of coffee. I had to pour it out as soon as I got home and wished I had tasted it while in the cafe because it was a waste of my money and I gave a tip. I'm not sure if this was just a bad day for the barista, but I really can't believe all of these reviews if the coffee always taste like this.
Only gave it 4-stars because the coffee was decent. Not amazing....but not horrible. My sandwich was delicious .
Soooo good! Love the bacon egg and cheese croissant. And Matcha Latte!
Great gourmet coffee house, the staffs are friendly. The Vietnamese coffee with condensed milk is not good.
Fantastic as always. They have the best beans, the best equipment, and the staff is top notch. Highly recommend.
Love this coffee shop! Their seasonal drinks are so good!
Amazing customized coffee.

Favorite coffee shop! Everyone is friendly and try to make you something your happy with. Espresso is delicious with 5 different roasts. Sandwiches are always made fresh and hit the spot! I love the atmosphere too, not too big or small with a spacious patio. I'm a regular there.

Great coffee (and I'm saying that as a frequent Seattle traveler) and amazing atmosphere. Relaxing, calm, and focused. Exactly what a coffee shop should be. I got sick of the bustle at Starbucks. Great food too! Well-priced and good portions, very much unlike Starbucks in that respect. Very nice & quick staff.
Banana nut bread & coffee fresh!

Fantastic cappuccinos and breakfast.  Told my son for years (that liked coffee) he needed to try a cappuccino.  Bright him to Waterbean, and he is sold.  And so am I... great flavor... love this place.
The atmosphere is very intimate and relaxing. I had the East and West Sandwich and it was delicious and the coffee was amazing!
This is a great little coffee shop nestled in a little strip mall of other businesses. The employees are always super kind and the coffee is delicious. You can't go wrong with a little treat either!

Walked in. Waited give or take ten minutes. Walked out. Young man working behind the counter never acknowledged my presence nor the young lady who arrived after me. Walked out. Can't comment on any of the food or coffees. Food didn't look at all appealing being prepared for others. My office is in the business park and I shan't be returning.
When we lived in Charlotte we loved coming here. Very nice chill environment. Loved the added touch of the chocolate covered coffee bean on top of your coffee cup.
Loved the cinnamon dulcet latte and croissant breakfast sandwich!!
Best Chai I have ever had!

The experience at this Waterbean Coffee location in Charlotte was pretty good. We visited for a quick coffee and snack during brunch hours on a weekday.

We got the mocha, a cookie and a scoop of icecream. The mocha was delightful, and so was the coconut flavoured icecream. We didn't care much for the cookie.

The service was prompt and polite, and it seemed like a busy location with most tables both inside and outside being occupied.

I recommend this Waterbean location if you're looking for a better-than-average coffee or snack.
First time heading over to Waterbean and can say it did not disappoint. Mocha was wonderful, and the gluten-free treat was amazing! Cannot wait to try something else on our next visit.

I went to Waterbean Coffee for the first time this morning. I ordered the Classic Cappuccino and bought a prepackaged sprinkled sugar cookie. Both were absolutely delicious. I can without a doubt say this is the BEST coffee I've ever tasted. You will not be disappointed at this coffee shop!
Coffee is good, service is just okay.

We were traveling through town and were lucky to find this place. The sandwiches were great and we really enjoyed the macrons. I'd highly recommend the pour over. It's strangely difficult to find a good pour over that is well balanced and takes advantage of the brewing method. This was it.

Had a great experience here! Not too far from the airport! Love that their iced drinks come in a cool glass! Asked for a "for here" mug because I love drinking my lattes in a mug. It came with a beautiful design. Their croissant breakfast sandwiches were perfect for what we needed.
Loves this little gem. Good coffee and awesome food!
The food is great. Didn't taste any coffee in my cappuccino...
Expected more of a variety when it came to the sandwiches,  as shown on website

Okay so I wanted to hate this place so bad because the service was absolutely horrible butttttt the coffee that I got was amazing better than Starbucks pretty shocking  do not buy the banana nut bread in less you like a ridiculous amount of nuts there's more nuts than bread.
Went here on a morning that I was feeling lazy and didn't want to make breakfast.  The coffee was tasty quick service and my sandwich was tasty as well
Treat in a glass
I loved the coffee from there (macchiato)

Decent coffee but the barista was rude and uninterested. No greeting, barely spoke, and when I asked for a recommendation since I had never been all he said was "I drink black coffee". That's it. No recommendations, not even for black coffee. Disappointing to say the least since I've always heard good things. Won't be back.
Great coffee! I recommend their seasonal drinks. I ordered the coconut English toffee latte and it was the perfect way to start my day.

I have been going to the same location for almost a year now.  I went there today to get my same order and she told me the price.  I asked her say that again.  She tells me they went up on the price. I tell her you went from $5.60 to $8.63 for 1 drink!!!! I asked her why didn't they change the price on the board and she stands there looking lost. Well I won't be going back. Very upset . I was trying to order a  Frozen caramel latte with a shot of expresso.
It's great depending on who's working that day. But overall it's consistent with there stock and quality. Drinks are a bit pricey.
Great place for a quick bite. When one person is working you'll wait a minute. But even then. Great food and great service.
Very good breakfast sandeich

I can't believe this place has 4.5 stars! Over priced and most definitely not worth a second try. Waited over an hour for a Vietnamese coffee and a croissant. The coffee was horribly wrong. It's supposed to be sweetened with condensed milk. It had maybe 1/2 a tea spoon worth. The croissant was burned dry and just over done. Not worth the wait!
Great pour over coffee and really cool atmosphere.
Super chill coffee bar off the beaten path.
Good coffee..sweet tea taste like poison.

takes entirely too long for 1 caramel iced coffee with extra caramel . its never made correctly, what's so hard about my simple caramel iced coffee, and today when I went back in and asked for more caramel in my iced coffee, the barista put something else in it instead of caramel and it tasted awful! total waste of $7 I will never return
Staff was friendly and the drink was pretty good. A little pricey, but beats the pants off Starbucks. Can't wait to go back!

Great coffee and great ambience. I would suggest trying their seasonal beverages. It's a peaceful place to sit and work. You get some pastries and quite bite options here. We tried their macaroons. While the taste was great, the texture was chewy rather than airy.
Great coffee and quiet place... it would be nice if they keep the outside tables cleaner
Nice place for coffee, ice cream and simple sandwiches.

I went to this Waterbean on Monday September 26 around 10:45 am and there was a guy working. I asked for extra oat milk in my coffee and even paid for it, as my cup of coffee was $10.00 for a vanilla latte. I received my drink and it didn't the extra oat milk, so I asked for a little more. His response was "oh well milk prices are really high right now." I was very confused as I've never received that response from any restaurant/coffee shop. This was one of the worst customer service experiences I've ever had. Do not go in here if he's working.
A wonderful coffee shop! Great coffee, friendly baristas! The tea selection is nothing to skip over! Definitely a shop you need to visit!

Iced coffee, smoothies, and croissants were all a huge hit in my group. The place is cute and the employees were kind. Some of the macarons were great and soft as they should be, but some of them were actually hard leading me to believe they were a couple days old since they're usually soft for a couple days after being made or defrosted.

Horrible coffee , ordered pumpkin spice latte with oat milk and I paid $7.50 with tax for that. It literally tasted like a k-cup hot chocolate with artificial flavoring that I wasn't able to distinguish and tell what it is. You want good coffee this isn't the place.

Coffee was delicious, and they even had a vegan orange-chocolate muffin! I got a mocha with macadamia milk and the texture was perfect.  Customer service was great. Would definitely come again; it is a wonderful environment.
Great vibe, great service, great breakfast sandwich, fantastic drink combos, I love it here!

My and my coworkers have been coming here for years. There was ONE time where the macarons weren't fresh and they immediately fixed it. I love coming here and I don't think I've ever had anything I didn't enjoy. Definitely should give them a try if you're in the area.

I truly had an amazing experience here. I was in town for job training and the night before I ate here was just awful. So when I woke up and found this place I was so excited to give it a try! Their drinks are amazing and their breakfast was so yummy. I got there as soon as they opened and the lady working was so nice and helpful. If I ever return to Charlotte I will absolutely come back here!

Absolutely horrible customer service. I went in this morning there were 2 employees and 2 customer (I was one of the two). I asked for a turkey, egg, & cheese croissant. I am pregnant and pregnant women cannot eat deli meat unless it is cooked. I asked the cashier if they could put the meat on the skillet to make it safe to eat for my child. As the other employee was 3 steps away frying an egg on a skillet she said "No, she could not do that because she might burn herself." You could burn yourself frying an egg, or using the toaster (as she was currently doing). If she is that incompetent she probably shouldnt be cooking anything. It was laziness and racial profiling. I will NEVER go to waterbean again. Moms all over ban this place. They care less about you or your babies!
Barista was polite and honest about drink recommendations. Iced Coffee is strong and tastes good! I'll be visiting again next time I'm in the area

Not usually in this area but it was convenient and breakfast is difficult to do poorly. Pretty basic order of drip coffee and a croissant which only list meats so I asked if they come with egg? Yes the barista replied, I ordered the dream which had bacon. While the sandwich is being prepared I added cream to my coffee and it curdled. I tried to let them know the little bit of creamer they had was bad and they should refill it. It was explained to me that creamer always curdles because the coffee is hot and did not want to replace it nor my cup. I then had to explain that I drink coffee every morning for the past 20+ years and I prefer non curdled creamer. I was glad to leave until I checked my sandwich that has no egg. Just a croissant with bacon... really! Who eats these things? One of them had salami on it, is that even a thing? I could only imagine how the conversation would go when addressing this problem with the non helpful baristas so I chalk it up to a learning experience and will never return to this establishment. Perhaps I can go by another breakfast spot and order some eggs to go on my meatissant and enjoy my curdled coffee. It's a shame because now all the surrounding breakfast options are jumping out at me as I leave... regrettable
Not sure why these reviews are so high. I'm a bit of a coffee aficionado and the coffee here is very mediocre. I would rather go to Starbucks.
Very nice location and great food!!! Not to mention incredible staff :) Definitely coming here again!!
Creme Brulee Latte was already broken this time :(
Just got a drip coffee there and it was one of the worst I've ever had, second only to a hospital vending machine.   Chain coffeehouses at their worst.
Cute little place and a nice atmosphere. My tea was pretty good.

I stopped in today for the first time. The staff is so inviting and welcoming. Very clean and lovely decor. My daughter got the kids ice cream with sprinkles. She loved it , especially the birthday cake macaroon. I got the green tea frappe, which was amazing along with the croissant ham, egg, and cheese sandwich with spinach. We can't wait to come back and try more things on the menu!
Excellent customer service.  Wonderful selection.  Very clean and well maintained.  Great atmosphere.
Clean place but the barista didn't know what a cortado was and a wobbly chair fell apart.
Great awesome place
Good coffee and a great atmosphere!
Good coffee!!
Great coffee! Very nice ambiance and decor
The coffee is so smooth and delicious.   The macaroons are pretty awesome too.
New to the area and searched for a coffee shop that had variety in there menu. Waterbean coffee has great options of different coffee and surprisingly great food. Will be my go to spot from now on.
Love the ice white mocha and build your own breakfast sandwich that they make fresh or order will definitely go again!!!
Vietnamese coffee was delicious
First time there and was great , there coffee is the best so far way better then Starbucks , be sure to check this place out for all your coffee needs and fixes ........
Blueberry muffin was delicious and both workers were very sweet. If I have to stop by MEPS again, I'll make sure to head over!
Great little coffee shop off of 485, in the Whitehall business park.
Overall really good. I just didn't know they were going to add Sriracha mayo(?) To my bacon egg and cheese bagel  which was an unpleasant surprise.
Expensive

Great place to study/work. Lots of seating inside and outside. Food smelled amazing, coffee was very good. They had chill, ambient, lyricless music playing, which I appreciated since I was trying to work.

The first time we came here it was great, but each successive time we come the service gets worse. Food is fine, Coffee is fine, but there is one particular worker who routinely has a bad attitude. Usually we come in, order, and go sit outside waiting for our food to be brought out to our table. Today, it was packaged to go (we didn't order to go) and just placed up with the mobile orders with no communication at all, so it just sat there until I ventured in to see if the packaged food was indeed ours. It clearly seems that the particular employee does not want to serve any customers on her shift so we are happy to try out the queen city tea bar around the corner next time instead.

Always love coming here. Try out the different espresso roasts! My favorite is the eternity espresso with their hazelnut or coconut syrup. They also have ice cream and breakfast sandwiches, what else could you want?! Clean and spacious with super cute vibes for studying or chatting with friends. Give them a try!

The attitude of a girl serving in the Morning of 8th August was pathetic.
If customer asks a question, she should respond properly!
Great coffee
Really good coffee!
Visiting from out of town, was going to traditional Starbucks but I'm glad I didn't.....Amazing!
Great service from Morgan.
Good breakfast but limited choices.
The place is decorated so nicely and created a serene atmosphere. The coffee and other beverage selections are great.
Honestly the best coffee I've ever had, thank you to Morgan and Valeria for making our food and beverages while being so informative and kind! Definitely will come back again
My first time there, delicious iced coffee. It was pretty much empty when I went so service was quick.
Great Iced Creme Brulee coffee  on a hot day!
Atmosphere is so calm and friendly, food is great and service is small town feel.

Nice place. Good coffee. Plenty of parking and no line around the building like the Starbucks down the road. Ice cream if you're not solely interested in caffeine. Friendly staff. Plenty of inside seating and an outside area too.

Such an awesome place! My coworkers and I go here all the time.  Their coffee and croissants are amazing and the boba tea they recently started serving is awesome as well! All staff members are always super polite. I highly recommend Waterbean!
I went there this morning and Morgan was amazing at giving us suggestions and made the best coffee I think I've ever had. Would highly recommend to everyone.
went for the first time today and Morgan was amazing and explained everything perfectly, would 10/10 come back! she did amazing with my latte!

Morgan was super helpful and personable.  She was also very patient with our order since we had a very particular one.  Would definitely come back again because of the customer service, and I don't even drink coffee.

March 2021
Hello you . I'm not a coffee  drinker by any means but went to check out this place out with my good friend. Cute, quaint, and nice place with warm lighting and lots of natural lighting through the windows - good place to do work or hang out. The person at the cash register was friendly and informative and told us about the different options and types (French press, Vietnamese style, and Aeropress) of brewing the coffee . We ended up getting the coffee flight, which is an array of three types of coffee to your choosing. We got the Honduras, Ethiopia, and Guatemala brews. I'm a basic coffee drinker (ice vanilla latte  when I do drink) so I didn't really know how much I should've appreciated these different types of coffee. I doused that shiii in cream and sugar  so ofc it tasted good in the end haha.

If you're a coffee drinker, I definitely recommend you give this place a try. The vibes are well worth it.

1st time here, coffee was delicious. I ordered the Cream brulee iced Latte, strong coffee with pudding at the bottom. Highly recommended. They also serve ice cream and macaroons. Nice place with limited power outlets.
Great coffee and atmosphere.
Nice place. Great drinks. They have MACARONS. And sandwiches.
Good coffee , nice service

Really good place but the stars are due to today's service. Not sure how else to bring this across to whoever runs this place. Walk in with expectation of having drinks and food with my wife and kids. The girl at the counter tells us she can't make the food just the coffee. I had no clue that certain people specialized in specifics. More training needed for these employees to be able to serve full menu.
Great coffee, friendly staff and COVID-19 compliant!
nice place for coffee and hanging
Excellent coffee and the sauce they use on the croissant is amazing!

Lindo sitio, excelente atencion de la chica, muy buen cafe y excelente cafe que fue lo que consumi y lo que me gusta mas, tiene mas opciones como distintos tipos de helados. WiFi libre para clientes. Buen sitio de encuentro.

Depending on who is working, the ice coffee is amazing. The lady with the pink hair (sorry I don't know her name) made the most amazing ice coffee. You could taste the coffee and the hint of flavors. But today with going back the flavors are overpowering the coffee and it doesn't taste good.
Best cold brew coffee in Charlotte. Helpful staff, too.

Great breakfast sandwiches, plenty of seating, and strong WiFi. Decent selection of sweets and they have ice cream. Some of the sweets are on a rotation, so if you have a fave they may not have it at certain times. Service can be hit or miss depending on who you get. Coffee is Ok...but it's free refills if you dine in.
My oat milk latte was delicious, staff is friendly, place is cute & clean with outdoor seating and plenty of parking.
Muy rico, very delicious!
Great hidden gem in South Charlotte. Small and quaint with friendly and attentive staff. Love that the sandwiches are made fresh to order. Nice spot for a quick bite and a cup of coffee.
Super cute atmosphere and really good coffee.  Was a good place for a casual business meeting!!
Great place! Really great coffee selection and Macaroons!!
Great espresso! Nice vibe inside. Other options looked good but we didn't try them. Definitely worth it to stop here instead of the million Starbucks in the area.
Amazing portions, perfectly cooked food and one of the best coffees I've had. They even do lunch!
Great coffee, great prices
Delicious coffee!

I was super happy to discover this locally owned joint on my way to a Starbucks. They've got good coffee and (to my surprise) great *actual* food options if you need lunch. Everybody I've encountered is super friendly, and the vibe is airy and relaxed. They've even got an outdoor section. Happy to support this local enterprise
Gteat local spot for coffee. Baristas are really knowledgeable on beans and various drinks.
ldh wfDl qhwh
This place is amazing! Close to Steele Creek and it's a hidden gem! Their coffees are brewed literally like the old school coffee shops with pride and care in how it looks in the cup! So good
One of the best coffee shops ive been to in the area.
Enjoy getting coffee from any of their locations. They have macadamia nut milk which is an added bonus.
This place makes Starbucks look like a joke, great hospitality. And you can actually taste the great quality of coffee. All they need is bigger cups.

Lived in this area for years and about time a new coffee shop open up. Great choice of sandwiches and tea. Friendly and welcoming staff.  There's also beer on tap.

The coffee was great. My only issue was that they use american cheese, which we all know isn't cheese, and up charged to use different cheese.

Great coffee. Staff seemed to be new but that's not a problem. Did I mention the coffee was great? Lots of sweet snack options including gluten free as well, although I did not try any. Plenty of parking available and service was pretty quick as well. Would recommend the coffee to anyone and will consider coming back to check out their food options
Had breakfast there.  Very disappointed with the Vietnamese Coffee as it was very weak.  The color of the coffee looks more like tea.
Very lovely place and very fresh!! Great place to relax
Great aeropress and French press brews.  Also, great breakfast sandwich croissants!
Perfect before work and great customer service
Kind people, good coffee, great music playing, calm atmosphere
Thuong hieu ca fe moi o MY
Very good. Very fresh.
The guys are so sweet. I just love my hot chocolate. Go visit you won't be disappointed.
Can actually make a cappuccino here unlike every other coffee shop
The iced mocha frappuccino is very good, not too much coffee, not too sweet like starbucks & the crossiants are flakey and filling. Service was quick and friendly!
Cold brew is on point!
Great coffee, food, and service
Excellent coffee, great people, and a great food menu, too.

I was visiting the area and wanted to try something new. There was only 1 person in the establishment to take orders, make drinks, cook food, and deliver food to tables, so service was a bit slow.

I ordered their signature Sizzlewich and a sugar free caramel, almond latte. I didn't care for the waterbean sauce, which was just your typical Yum Yum sauce. Overall, it was fairly decent.

The establishment itself was very clean and "modern hippie chic."  The display was various desserts was very tempting.
Loved finding this place that offers craft coffee in the south Charlotte area. They offer Chemex's and single origin coffee and teas!
Great place!
Good quality, great customer service.
Always nice and good prices
Nice coffees on the brew!
The food is amazing and the staff are really personable and have great customer service.. Thank you!!
Great friendly service (9/29/19 AM) and excellent latte.
Cold brew is on point.

Spent most of my day here getting some work done while traveling. The ambience is so inviting and relaxing. The staff and the food are great! Annie was such a doll. Thank you! Looking forward to visiting again one of your other locations.
Super cool place,  coffee was more than excellent.
Nice coffee, nice people.
Loved it! Excellent hot and cold cafe latte. We also got a BLTS and it hit the spot. Very friendly staff too
Fantastic coffee! I loved the volcano, very different and tasty. I tried coconut in my coffee and it is honestly the best flavor I've added.
Always great coffee
Very tasty coffee, very nice service.
FINALLY an independent coffee shop on the south side of town. fantastic location and great mojo in here. the mocha was stellar and they have gluten free and vegan muffins! will def be returning.
What a delicious breakfast croissant with ham and cheese and an egg. The guy working there made it a work of art. Well Worth the wait.

hmmm.. I ordered a cappuccino but received a beverage that appeared to be an espresso with some milk foam on top of it. Not bad espresso it was but it definitely was not a cappuccino. Weird. Barista skills have some area for improvement.
Great local coffee shop with a solid food menu. Also serves draft beer.
Love the Vietnamese coffee with condensed milk!
A wide assortment of teas and coffee type drinks. There's an outdoor patio you can go for conversation. It has a very relaxing feel just walking in.
Good coffee and ambiance
Eating is plentiful, Good food, good coffee, good service. Parking is a snap.
Macaroons and French Pressed coffee done right!!!!!
Great place and great staff.  The food was great

For my first time been there it was awsome specially becuase of the employees victoria and sarah both helped me explaining the menu and even after i order and got my cofee and food they walked up to me and ask if i needed anything. They both went above and beyond on customer service 10/10 on everything i will come back for sure .

This place is great for coffee, breakfast, lunch, and sweets! I come here all the time for coffee! They're so good and you can tell they take the care to do a good job! The croissant sandwich is one of my fave breakfast items. They started doing sushi and poke bowls here and they're absolutely delicious!
Love their coffee and the ham, salami, cheese and egg croissants with their home sauce.  Awesome customer service from the staff.
Modern minimalist interior. Presentation was on point. However, latte was on the watery side and the sizzlewich was a bit undercooked.

It's smaller and not as cozy as Hunterville location,  but very clean inside.  The girls behind the counter were friendly and welcoming.  The mocha I ordered was absolutely better than Starbucks.  I like how they have different milk alternatives like oatmilk and macadamia nut, which I will try on a future visit. I will definitely return.
Friendly and knowledgeable baristas. They do French press, aeropress, pour overs, siphon brews, cold brew, etc. They do it all!
Friendly staff and FAST SERVICE!!!

Don't know her name, but the newly-made manager (overheard her talking to someone else) yesterday is awesome and very friendly! I would come back to this coffee shop because of her and a nice atmosphere as well as very good coffee!
Cute cafe! Cozy place to chill. Friendly staff! Did a photo shoot there.
Friendly service and delicious coffee & tea!
Such a little gem! Amazing coffee and treats.

Wow!  This is a huge upgrade to a coffee shop!  Stopped by here while I was in town for work.  So glad I stopped by.  Their specialty coffee drink is the Volcano.  It was awesome.  It has layers to it, including a little bit of heat.  Also they do coffee and espresso tastings!  Seriously who does that???  You need to check them out.

Plenty of seating if you want to come, hangout and do some work!

Ordered a BLT and a Chia Latte w/ espresso. On my sandwich I asked for no Tomatoes, I'm allergic to them. The girl at the cash register said ok so no lettuce, told her yes lettuce but no tomatoes. So then she replied ok no mushrooms and do you want mustard or mayo? This went on for about 2 minutes, because she got my order correct no tomatoes or onions or mushrooms since apparently a BLT comes with all of that. Fast forward to when I am back at work about to eat my sandwich, just to see that there was extra tomatoes in my food, if I had eaten that it would've been severe. All in all I would recommend the Latte but I would not recommend the food and if you do then please stress what you do not want on it, even if it does not say it, or else you'll feel like I did during work without a lunch.

Laid back place, very nice place located in shopping center,  few parking spaces in front of it, but additional parking spaces on the opposite side. You can sit inside or outside which is always nice during summer time. The employees were super nice and courteous,  they are willing to redo anything if don't like it, nice place quite place if you wanna read a book, study or just have a nice chat. Their coffee was good as well, they also have a good dessert selection.

Nice atmosphere, but kind of basic with the mod feel. As a passionate barista, I feel the "iced coffee's they're famous for isn't up to par. It tastes burnt similarly like Starbucks. Smoothies we're insane $5 for just some syrup and was so sugary. All the prices are outragous tbh. But I like the Thai tea! :/

What a fantastic place. I pass by all the time. I'm glad I decided to stop. Very serious coffee paired with a sweet helpful staff. I'll become a regular.  Very clean and modern with a fresh pallet of food for a coffe/tea shop. Easy in and out from Arrowood Rd and adjacent business park.
Ducked in here after outlet mall shopping. Great coffee and service!

Pleasantly surprised.
Stopped in on a Sunday afternoon and was warmly greeted.
Both the iced mocha and Americano were better than expected. Smooth and delicious.
It has a friendly atmosphere, limited seating but was a genuinely nice first experience.
Lots  of menu options (coffees, espressos, teas, and food items.)
Definately worth a repeat visit.
Very clean establishment
Only ordered a breakfast sandwich, but it was really good!
Prices were outrageous in my opinion. I asked about the macarons, they were almost $3 each. I bought a single lunch meal with a strawberry smoothie and spent over $21.

Also known as Sizzlewich, but the coffee here at Waterbean is very good! Had a French Press coffee and it was so smooth. Excellent service as well. Nice relaxing environment with a bar and tables. Come for for some great food and/or coffee!
Great coffee, great food and an awesome atmosphere near Ayrsley. Nice to have quality inn the area vs the overpriced swill that is Starbucks.
